<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US>Hi, hwloc-devel<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;I
cannot find the code branch from &#8220;src/topology-x86.c &#8220;which can support for
32-bit APIC ID and CPUID leaf 0xb of Intel&#8217;s new processors. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:21.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'>So I think current hwLoc cannot support for latest Intel
CPU with </span><b><span lang=EN-US style='color:#00B0F0'>x2APIC</span></b><span
lang=EN-US style='color:#1F497D'>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:21.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:21.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'>Linux kernel 2.6.30 or following version already supports
this hardware feature <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:42.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'>and uses CPUID leaf 0xb to recognize the topology for more
than 1024 logical processors in SGI&#8217;s super computer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:10.5pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:15.75pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'>I think hwloc could also support this. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:15.75pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:15.75pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#948A54'>The following docs from Intel give details about x2APIC:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:31.5pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#948A54'>http://www.intel.com/Assets/PDF/appnote/241618.pdf<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:31.5pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#948A54'>http://www.intel.com/Assets/pdf/manual/318148.pdf<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:15.75pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#948A54'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;or &lt;&lt;Intel&reg; 64 Architecture
Processor Topology Enumeration&gt;&gt;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:15.75pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:15.75pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='color:#1F497D'>Thanks<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#1F497D'>Wei Lin <o:p></o:p></span></p>

